I shall here record another excursion to the savageS, which, though completed in less time than the former, was productive of more advan- tage. A company of Spaniards were employed in preparing the herb of Paraguay on the south- ern banks of the river Empalado. The trees from which these leaves were plucked failing, they commissioned three men to seek for the tree in request beyond the river. By accident they lit upon a hovel and a field of maize, from which they falsely con j ectured that the wood was full of savage hordes.
